##)Conditions:
--------------

*)Conditions are used to execute tasks only when a specified condition is true. 

*) If the condition is true, the task will be executed. If the condition is false, the task will be skipped.

*)Conditions are written using the "when" keyword.

*)Conditions can be used with variables, facts, and expressions.

*) The "when" keyword is used to define conditions in Ansible playbooks.

Memory Tip:
-----------

Condition = True  → Task Runs
Condition = False → Task Skips

  
Syntax:

- name: Task Name
  module_name:
    parameter: value
  when: condition
  
  
Example-1:
----------


- name: Conditions
  hosts: local
  connection: local

  vars:
    NUMBER: 9

  tasks:
  - name: print whether the given number is less than 20
    ansible.builtin.debug:
      msg: "Given number is: {{ NUMBER }} less than 20"
    when: NUMBER < 20
	
	
Example-2:
----------

- name: facts
  hosts: local
  connection: local
  become: yes

  tasks:
  - name: Install nginix if OS is Redhat
    ansible.builtin.dnf:
      name: nginix
      state: latest
    when: ansible_os_family == "RedHat"

  - name: Install nginix if OS is Redhat
    ansible.builtin.apt:
      name: nginix
      state: latest
    when: ansible_os_family == "Debian"
	

