##)FACTS:
---------

*)Facts are target server information collected automatically by Ansible. 
  Gathering Facts is the process of collecting that information before executing tasks in a playbook.
  
*)Facts are used to retrieve server information and make decisions in playbooks using facts.

*)ansible_facts is a built-in variable that stores all facts collected from the target server.
  ansible_facts → Contains all collected server information.

*)ansible_os_family → One specific fact inside the collected facts.

*)The "ansible_" prefix is used to refer the facts collected automatically by Ansible and to avoid conflicts with user-defined variables.

Ex: ansible_hostnames
    ansible_distribution
    ansible_os_family


Examples of Facts:
------------------

Hostname
IP Address
OS Family
Distribution
Memory Information
CPU Information
Disk Information

Example-1:
----------

- name: facts
  hosts: local
  connection: local
  become: yes

  tasks:
  - name: Install nginix if OS is Redhat
    ansible.builtin.dnf:
      name: nginix
      state: latest
    when: ansible_os_family == "RedHat"

  - name: Install nginix if OS is Redhat
    ansible.builtin.apt:
      name: nginix
      state: latest
    when: ansible_os_family == "Debian"
	
	
LOOPS:
------

*) Loops are used to execute the same task multiple times with different values.
*) Loops help avoid writing the same task repeatedly.

Use Case:
---------
 
*)When the same task needs to be performed on multiple items.

Syntax:
-------

- name: Task Name
  module_name:
    parameter: "{{ item }}" # item is a reserved keyword that holds the value being processed in the loop.
  loop:
    - value1
    - value2
    - value3


*)item --> item contains the current value being processed in the loop


Example-1:
----------

- name: Loops
  hosts: local
  connection: local # Ansible is connecting to localhost

  tasks: 
  - name: print names
    ansible.builtin.debug:
      msg: " Hello {{ item }}" # item is reserved keyword

    loop:
    - Megham
    - Aaranya
    - Bujji
    - Sailendra
	
	
Example-2:
----------

- name: configure packages
  hosts: local
  connection: local
  become: yes

  tasks:
  - name: packages
    ansible.builtin.package:
      name: "{{ item.name }}"   # refers name key
      state: "{{ item.state }}" # refers state key

    loop:
    - { name: "nginix", state: "absent"}
    - { name: "mysql", state: "absent"}
    - { name: "zip", state: "latest"}
	
###IMP)Important Points:
------------------------

*) {{ item }} is used when the loop contains simple values.

*) {{ item.key_name }} is used when the loop contains dictionary (key-value pair) data.